message.entry: System object String Set with allowed values:
StringSet requires a set of entries specified by a cell array of character vectors or a string array.
The {0} property must be set to a character vector or string scalar.
"{0}" is not a valid value for the {1} property. Valid values are: {2}.
"{0}" is not a valid type option for the {1} property. Valid type option values are: {2}.
StringSets must be created with a cell array of character vectors or a string array.
The list of allowed values passed to a StringSet must not contain empty entries.
The list of allowed values for a StringSet must be case-insensitive unique.
The list of allowed values provided to a StringSet must contain at least one element.
